Strong Password Checker (Java)

A Java console application that evaluates the strength of passwords and gives real-time feedback. Helps users create secure passwords using uppercase, lowercase, numbers, special characters, and minimum length rules.

Project Overview

This project demonstrates Java programming, regex, and conditional logic. It scores passwords based on multiple criteria and categorizes them as Weak, Medium, Strong, or Very Strong.

Features

Check password strength with clear feedback

Evaluates multiple criteria:

Minimum 8 characters

Uppercase letters

Lowercase letters

Numbers

Special characters

Interactive console interface

Categorizes password strength (Weak â†’ Very Strong)

